def: The state or condition of being feathery.
The common yellow-flowered avens of Europe (Geum urbanum); herbbennet. The name is sometimes given to other plants, as the hemlock,valerian, etc.
One who, or that which, spouts.
A small cart or wagon, as those used on the tramways in minesto carry coal or rubbish; also, a barrow or truck for shiftingbaggage, as at railway stations.
A vacant space, or gap, esp. between teeth in a jaw.
An agreeing to the action of another, by some act which bindsthe person in law.

Pertaining to treason; consisting of treason; involving thecrime of treason, or partaking of its guilt.Most men's heads had been intoxicated with imaginations of plots andtreasonable practices. Clarendon.
